{"title":"Quote a Word Expert","lesson":"L1 · HTML Foundations · Semantic Text Elements","desc":"Build a tiny fact card about language. Use <code>&lt;dfn&gt;</code> for a special term, <code>&lt;q&gt;</code> for a short quote, and <code>&lt;blockquote&gt;</code> for a longer quoted sentence.","startFile":"html","goals":[{"id":"has-dfn","label":"Uses a <dfn> term","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"<dfn[\s>]","flags":"i","minCount":1},{"id":"has-q","label":"Uses a short inline <q> quote","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"<q[\s>]","flags":"i","minCount":1},{"id":"has-blockquote","label":"Uses a <blockquote> for a longer quote","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"<blockquote[\s>]","flags":"i","minCount":1}],"targetHtml":"<section style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;max-width:520px;padding:12px;border:2px solid #d7d7d7;border-radius:10px;background:#fafafa;line-height:1.5;">
  <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Word of the Day</h2>
  <p><dfn>Onomatopoeia</dfn> is a word that sounds like the noise it names.</p>
  <p>One student said, <q>This is a fun word to say!</q></p>
  <blockquote style="margin:10px 0 0 0;padding-left:12px;border-left:4px solid #999;">Words can paint sounds in your mind before you even hear them.</blockquote>
</section>","targetSub":"A small card with a defined term, a short quote, and a longer quote.","files":{"guide":{"html":"<!-- This section groups the whole mini fact card into one clear area. -->
<section>
  <!-- A heading tells readers what this card is about. -->
