{"title":"Build a Banner with a Background","lesson":"L1 · HTML Foundations · HTML Images and Lists","desc":"Create a simple banner section and connect it to CSS with a class name. Then use the CSS <code>background-image</code> property to place an image behind the banner text. 🌄","startFile":"html","goals":[{"id":"has-banner-section","label":"Has a section for the banner","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"<section[\s>]","flags":"i","minCount":1},{"id":"has-banner-class","label":"Banner section uses class="banner"","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"class\s*=\s*["'][^"']*banner[^"']*["']","flags":"i","minCount":1},{"id":"has-heading","label":"Banner includes a heading","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"<h1[\s>]","flags":"i","minCount":1},{"id":"uses-background-image","label":"CSS sets a background image","target":"css","kind":"css_declaration","rule":"background-image\s*:\s*url\s*\(","flags":"i","minCount":1}],"targetHtml":"<section style="background-image:url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500530855697-b586d89ba3ee?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&q=80');background-size:cover;background-position:center;color:white;padding:40px 20px;border-radius:12px;text-align:center;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><h1 style="margin:0;">Mountain Camp</h1><p style="margin:12px 0 0;">Adventure starts here.</p></section>","targetSub":"A rounded banner with white text on top of a photo background.","files":{"guide":{"html":"<!-- This section holds the banner content on the page. -->
<!-- The class name "banner" lets the CSS target this element and add the background image. -->
<section class="banner">
  <!-- The main heading tells the viewer what the banner is about. -->
  <h1>Mountain Camp</h1>

  <!-- A short paragraph adds a simple message under the heading. -->
  <p>Adventure starts here.</p>
</section>","css":"/* Style the banner section so the background image can be seen clearly. */
.banner {
  /* Add the picture behind the banner content. */
  background-image: url("https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500530855697-b586d89ba3ee?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&q=80");

  /* Cover fills the whole section with the image. */
  background-size: cover;

  /* Center keeps the important part of the image in view. */
  background-position: center;

  /* White text is easier to read on the photo. */
  color: white;

  /* Padding creates space inside the banner. */
  padding: 40px 20px;

  /* Rounded corners make the banner look softer. */
  border-radius: 12px;

  /* Center the text inside the banner. */
  text-align: center;

  /* A simple font keeps the design clean. */
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

/* Remove default top spacing and keep the heading neat. */
.banner h1 {
  margin: 0;
}

/* Add a little space above the paragraph, but not too much. */
.banner p {
  margin: 12px 0 0;
}","js":"// No JavaScript needed for this challenge."},"pair":{"html":"<!-- Add a banner section and give it the class "banner". -->
