{"title":"Style a Table Border","lesson":"L1 · HTML Foundations · HTML Tables","desc":"Build a small table and apply border styling with CSS using <code>border-style</code>, <code>border-collapse</code>, and <code>border-color</code>. Add the CSS inside a <code>&lt;style&gt;</code> tag in your HTML so the table looks neat and colorful 🎨","startFile":"html","goals":[{"id":"has-table","label":"Has a table","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"<table[\s>]","flags":"i","minCount":1},{"id":"uses-border-style","label":"Uses border-style in CSS","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"border-style\s*:\s*solid","flags":"i","minCount":1},{"id":"uses-border-collapse","label":"Uses border-collapse in CSS","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"border-collapse\s*:\s*collapse","flags":"i","minCount":1},{"id":"uses-border-color","label":"Uses border-color in CSS","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"border-color\s*:\s*[^;]+","flags":"i","minCount":1}],"targetHtml":"<div style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;max-width:320px;"><table style="border-collapse:collapse;"><tr><th style="border:3px solid #2b7a78;padding:8px;background:#def2f1;color:#17252a;">Animal</th><th style="border:3px solid #2b7a78;padding:8px;background:#def2f1;color:#17252a;">Sound</th></tr><tr><td style="border:3px solid #2b7a78;padding:8px;">Cat</td><td style="border:3px solid #2b7a78;padding:8px;">Meow</td></tr><tr><td style="border:3px solid #2b7a78;padding:8px;">Dog</td><td style="border:3px solid #2b7a78;padding:8px;">Woof</td></tr></table></div>","targetSub":"A 2-column table with one clean collapsed border color around each cell.","files":{"guide":{"html":"<style>
  /* The table uses collapsed borders so touching borders become one neat line */
  table {
    border-collapse: collapse;
  }

  /* These cells need visible borders, so we choose a solid line style */
  th,
  td {
    border-width: 3px;
    border-style: solid;
    border-color: #2b7a78;
    padding: 8px;
  }

  /* A light background helps the heading row stand out */
  th {
    background-color: #def2f1;
  }
</style>

<!-- The table shows two headings across the top -->
<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Animal</th>
    <th>Sound</th>
  </tr>
  <!-- Each new row adds one animal and its sound -->
  <tr>
    <td>Cat</td>
    <td>Meow</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Dog</td>
    <td>Woof</td>
  </tr>
</table>","css":"","js":""},"pair":{"html":"<table>
