{"title":"Club Scores Border Lab","lesson":"L1 · HTML Foundations · HTML Tables","desc":"Build a small score table and style its borders using an internal <code>&lt;style&gt;</code> block. Use <code>border-style</code>, <code>border-collapse</code>, and <code>border-color</code> so the table lines look neat and colorful ✨","startFile":"html","goals":[{"id":"has-table","label":"Has a table","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"<table[\s>]","flags":"i","minCount":1},{"id":"uses-border-style","label":"Uses border-style in the style block","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"border-style\s*:\s*solid","flags":"i","minCount":1},{"id":"uses-border-collapse","label":"Uses border-collapse on the table","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"border-collapse\s*:\s*collapse","flags":"i","minCount":1},{"id":"uses-border-color","label":"Uses border-color in the style block","target":"html","kind":"regex","rule":"border-color\s*:\s*[^;]+","flags":"i","minCount":1}],"targetHtml":"<div style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;display:inline-block"><table style="border-collapse:collapse;border:3px solid #2e86de"><tr><th style="border:3px solid #2e86de;padding:8px 12px;background:#eaf3ff">Team</th><th style="border:3px solid #2e86de;padding:8px 12px;background:#eaf3ff">Points</th></tr><tr><td style="border:3px solid #2e86de;padding:8px 12px">Red Foxes</td><td style="border:3px solid #2e86de;padding:8px 12px">12</td></tr><tr><td style="border:3px solid #2e86de;padding:8px 12px">Blue Owls</td><td style="border:3px solid #2e86de;padding:8px 12px">9</td></tr></table></div>","targetSub":"A 2-column score table with blue, collapsed borders.","files":{"guide":{"html":"<!-- The style tag lets us write CSS right inside the HTML file. -->
